<s> Thinking aloud here: That's an interesting point.  </s>
<s> I expect there will indeed be many applications that have additional constraints on the format of their XML documents, and it is likely that those constraints cannot be expressed in a DTD, using the current syntax.  </s>
<s> But as long as XML doesn't have the notion of a "profile", communicating a profile will have to be done out-of-band.  </s>
<s> A PI doesn't  </s>
<s> mean anything to anybody, unless (1) the XML spec says what it means, or (2) people exchanging XML agree on what it means (i.e., out-of-band).  </s>
<s> Note that the ?xml...? at the top *doesn't* establish the XML profile for SGML tools (assuming they can read XML).  </s>
<s> SGML tools simply don't know what a PI means.  </s>
<s> SGML may be modified by TC4 so that an occurrence of ?SGML some-fpi?  </s>
<s> at the top does indicate a profile, but currently it doesn't.  </s>
<s> If you want to support profiles of XML, you'll have to add it to the spec *now* and you have to state that ?something... some-url?  </s>
<s> is defined by XML to mean the profile with global identifier `some-url'.  </s>
<s> The `some-url' can point to the user-manual of the profile, or just to nothing at all.  </s>
